rComments: One of the kindest professors I have ever had who is always keen to help students. It was a very tough class for me as I had no prior coding experience but he was very considerate and was flexible with deadlines. Some lectures can be a bit heavy but he does his best to make it understandable. You will definitely learn a lot!
Great prof. Very clear in his explanations and can explain it more than 1 way. Take him for anything you can.

Provides videos of midterm and final exam material for everyone, since the course is really hard to comprehend. Not the most entertaining teacher, but much better than the rest. Also the assignments take up WAY too much time for 5%.

uses slides which makes it difficult to follow along. u should take the course with suren phan. he explains better than patrick. this course can be difficult, so use previous year's exams, no need to buy the textbook

Professor Patrick is a great prof! He really tries to make you like and understand statistics! He will do his best to keep you interested and to explain the use of everything. The subject matter is still hard and his assigments are ridiculous (too long for 5%), but still... He even made a review video online so you could watch and rewatch!
Like the others below mentioned, he's a great professor - Probably the best for statistics. The material itself, however, is killer and much harder than the 2303 prerequisite. Be warned.

Knows the subject very well, however explains issues and writes slides in too much mathematics. Some of the concepts are hard enough as they are, the additional math jargon and symbols only confuse people more. He is, however, available for additional help when required. I would rate him an "A" math professor and a "B+" Stats prof.

I have to say, out of all the professors at the University of Ottawa, Professor Patrick is probably one of the friendliest. He was always willing to make office hours available to students and he responds to e-mail's very quickly. The material itself isn't "extremely" easy, but he conveys it in an effective manner. Overall, I'd HIGHLY recommend him

This is the best teacher I have met at this university. He is genuinely interested in the students and will always be available to help you out. Has a good sense of humour and is always friendly. Beware that the course itself is hard and needs good mathematic background. Other than that the course is interesting.
